{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b8c240d3-d392-491f-9bc2-e8b6e48335a2","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates **`.ips` crash reports** when a process crashes. You don't need `createdump`.\n\n**Where to find them:**\n\n- **`~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — crash reports for your user\n- **`/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — system-wide crash reports\n\nLook for a file named like `YourAppName_YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS_machinename.ips`.\n\n**To view:**\n```bash\n# List recent crash reports\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/*.ips | head\n\n# Or open in Console.app\nopen -a Console\n```\n\n**For core dumps** (if you need a full memory dump), macOS disables them by default. You can enable them with:\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\nThen re-run your app — the core file will appear in `/cores/`.\n\nIf you have a `.ips` file with native frames from `libcoreclr.so` or the NativeAOT runtime, I can help symbolicate it using the **apple-crash-symbolication** skill.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"765fc149-cd45-4fff-b1b5-49249e5aed85","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without createdump. This is a diagnostic question — let me answer from knowledge.","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"4188:39A45D:63C6D0C:6CFBBAC:69F1632C"},"id":"c505c796-b9d3-4471-9894-1a3565144bd3","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:47:34.764Z","parentId":"4897747b-ee7d-40c1-9af4-8f9fc24f46eb"}
